caption: Is it the best thai I ever had....no. Bit if you add the decor and customer service you get five stars. Plus, it is a good deal.

Absolutely amazing food and service!!  We went as a group and they served us the most delicious appetizers.  The main course was several different plates of drunken noodles, fish, chicken fried rice, and more.  The dessert was a egg banana mix, fried, with a raspberry topping, and coconut ice cream!  We will definitely be back.
Wow panang beef Curry is to die for. Service good
Consistently tasty and fair pricing.
Been here several times and each time it gets better. Staff knows what I usually order. All around a great place.

The food here is SO good!! First discovered it four years ago on a layover and it has become a required stop every time my husband and I are in the Tampa area. HIGHLY recommend!! Every dish we’ve tried has been delicious, and mango sticky rice is a new fave after trying it here!

Such a unique, cool, and calming environment with amazing and authentic food. I had their soup, stir fry, and fried banana dessert. It all was great. Would definitely come back and recommend to friends.
Food is delicious and friendly service.
Great services, Pet friendly, And great food! Love it!
Great atmosphere and food! Lots of vegetarian and vegan options. I got the vegetable spring rolls, tofu soup, and tofu panang curry and it was all so delicious!!
Outstanding place for Thai food. Everyone at our table was quite pleased. I look forward to a return visit. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I liked.
Our go to Thai place
Great place for quality Thai food. Got there about one, it wasn't busy. I can see why they have a lot of positive reviews.

Hands down, the best Thai food in Tampa! Actually, their beef panag is the best I've ever had in the US. The customer service is great, and their lunch specials all come with soup and a small egg roll. Love love love this place!
Absolutely great Thai food, one of my new favorites. The chicken drunken noodle was excellent. We also had the fresh rolls in the tie rolls both of them excellent. I highly recommend this place.
Excellent food and fair prices. Lunch with a drink $13
A preferred spot for quality Thai food. i will be back with my coworkers. makes me feel like i in nashville again.
Massaman curry was very good!
Wonderful service, reasonable prices and delicious food. Eat here often during lunch.

I love calamari.  I make it a point to try as many places that have good ratings, and offer calamari.  This calimari is one, if not the worst I’ve had.  What’s the first thing that comes to mind when you see it? Me too, rubber.  It didn’t disappoint, as it tasted just like to felt, rubber. That didn’t set up the two entrees well.  Sigh, inflated reviews of Tampa hit again.  I honestly want to like these places as they are very close to where I live.  Sadly I will have to travel the 4-5 miles out to get quality food.  Less than a mile away, and food quality shouldn’t get to this level.. Spoke too soon.  This is after we had a small tasting of each entree (threw out the calamari). The last picture is what was left, and my wife wanted me to cook for her after we “ate”.  This was not appetizing at all, and no amount of glittering decorations at a restaurant could make us think differently..AGAIN, this is less than a mile from where we live..
Tom Yum soup was great. Black pepper garlic stir fry tasted really good though not really peppery or garlicky. Super friendly and accommodating;  low carb so they gave me extra veg instead.
thai food... so delicious. Service is always timely even when they have a full house.
Best Thai restaurant in Tampa

Best Thai restaurant and food in town, hands down!!! Always so full of the authentic flavors, presented artistically, and the wonderful staff and owners are just as well presented and kind ❤ They think of all of the details, from each addition to the art that surrounds you, down to the pop of color on the edible flowers :)
Great food and staff!!
The food and atmosphere was fantastic!

Excellent chicken dishes - basil and garlic pepper. Unless you like fatty meat, don't get the red pork. Wish they would bring paid online orders out to car, curbside on Franklin Street. Oddly, when I ordered online, a Royal Canin account was set up for me - I don't know if that was a strange coincidence or something related to the Active Menu program?
My fav spot for delicious Thai food. great place to relax, people watch, eat good food or all the above.  had a friend come into town and asked me to take him here again. prices are decent.

Half the portion size but twice the price. The food was good but just not what I expected with the high cost. I was very disappointed in the portion size. And the Crab Fried rice is not nearly as good as at otther Thai Restaurant in the Tampa area, no lump pieces of real crab meat, I was extremely disappointed. I would say, give them a try but try some of the other Thai restaurants locally as well.

Was there earlier with my husband. This restaurant was phenomenal with excellent service. We ordered the panang curry and green curry for lunch as our entree and it came with complimentary soup and egg roll also had the fried tofu. All were delicious. If you're looking for great authentic thai food with a beautiful ambiance this is a must try.
Always amazing food. Great service and worth going to again and again! Cant say enough good things, go check it out.
The Basil fried rice is to die for! Everything we ate was delicious. Highly recommend!
My favorite place for quality thai food. Dropped in on Mon I think. The staff was very friendly and kind. The bill was fair I would say.
My favorite location for delicious Thai food.
My go-to for lunches!
Thai food and the feeling here is excellent. Filled me up. The place has a cool feel to it. They have a lot of good reviews for a reason.

We had the best service when eating here. The waiters were so attentive and kind, it was refreshing. They did a great job following COVID guidelines. The pad thai was amazing. My husband loved his basil fried rice. Everything was great! We will definitely be returning.
A very posh Thai restaurant in downtown. Has very authentic taste. The quantity was a bit less but I always prefer quality than quantity. Worth every bucks. Must try!

Was excited to eat here prior to a show at Tampa Theatre. 20 mins to get a glass of wine. Fairly busy, but not even acknowledged for 15 mins. Ordered Si-am platter. Good food but not outstanding. Would eat here again but would hope for much better service
The food is amazing! The staff and owners are amazing! The atmosphere is wonderful! And it’s close to everything in downtown Tampa!
Today I went here for a take a way. There was an older homeless man who was asking for a job. The entire staff gentle with him. Keep up the kindness. 🌻😊
Beautiful atmosphere. Excellent service. Food was absolutely delicious. Drink list was limited. There was a lot of drug/wanderers near entrance due to a walk up alcohol wi.dow right next door.
The flavor... incredible. Even the Thai spring rolls were incredible. Chicken Satay to die for. My wife’s new favorite place.
Delicious food! Attention to detail in every aspect of the decor....great service...highly recommended!
Great service. Clean restaurant. Authentic food. Extremely flavorful. I will visit again.
Authentic and tasty food. Service is a little slow but nothing too serious.
Amazing and authentic Thai food.

Their price is a slightly higher (10-20%) than other casual thai places which I can only attribute to their downtown Tampa location.  Their food is good and better than other casual thai restaurants I have been to.  It is always packed at lunch time.
Mediocre at best.  Seafood pad Thai was not fresh seafood.  The sauce had little tamarind flavor.  Steamed dumplings were abysmal.  Garlic pepper chicken was best of the order.
Came here for a quick lunch. It was a clean and sophisticated looking restaurant. Fast and friendly service. Food was good.
The food is excellent and the presentation is as wonderful!  You will really enjoy your downtown lunch here!
Absolutely delicious, and really good service!
Incredible noodles and very nice staff

we had lunch there with 3 of my colleagues. Small portions, Salads are not authentic Thai and feels like pre-packed vegetables. Curries were good but nothing special. price is around $14 per person with water... not the best Thai..
Food quality is really and consistent. Also, service is really good however, it can get very busy during lunch hours so be prepared to wait a little.
Food amazing. Staff extremely friendly. They responded well when I requested authentic (Thai-style). Learn Gail and pad per fish outstanding.
Amazing service! I had a bowl of Tom Kha, jasmine rice, and fresh basil roll. The peanut sauce was a-mazing!
Wonderful delicious authentic Thai food. Love the green curry!
Delicious and lots of unique desert options! Beautifully decorated and friendly staff. Highly reccomend the pad see-ew!!
Excellent tastes and very fast service. Great and will be back when next in town
Great customer service and amazing food!
The good one .

Traditional well made Thai dishes in the heart of Tampa. Moderate lunch prices with flavorful chicken rice soup and crispy spring roll included. Six spice level ranging from none to Thai++. Our small party ran the gamut. Lost a star for slowness in taking our order.
The flavors are fantastic, which is the most important thing to know. The decor is amazing, along with the presentation and service. Easily the best Thai in the area.

I would eat here again.  They were busy but the service was good and the food was delicious!  I am on Atkins so I had a salad with peanut sauce and fried tofu! Yum! My brother got pad thai - thai hot - which was almost too hot for him - lol.

I absolutely love this place!  One of the best Thai restaurants in the Tampa Bay Area.  A very relaxed atmosphere, friendly and attentive staff, and delicious food!  The pad Thai and jasmine tea are my favorite things to order.  Highly recommend!
Love all the food Seasoning  just amazing S2

I can't speak for the food. We were seated and waited at least 20 minutes. No greeting, no water, etc.  We were in close eyesight of service bay and gave several servers "Please help us" looks and still nothing. We had horrible customer service. The server who pretended not to see us could at least have sent someone else.
So good we came a 2nd time in 2 days wonderful curry

Best fusion Thai in Tampa. Their duck is always flavorful and crispy. They have a crab fried rice that is to die for and their Thai tea is worth every penny. The decor is so very serene and the staff has great input for new folx. All in all, great restaurant!
When we go to Si-am Thaimerican we ten to order a few items and share. It's always delicious.  And the service is second to none.
Delicious food. Great staff.

One of my favorite restaurants in Tampa, I've been coming here for years. Everything is right: location in downtown Tampa next to the Tampa Theatre, beautiful decor, fine food and service, exceptionally personable owner, whose Thai wife is the chef. Try the shrimp panang and pineapple fried rice. Reasonable pricing.
Very good Thai restaurant with great waiters and waitresses.

I read the reviews before going here because it's been several years since I've  eaten here and I couldn't remember what the food taste like. I ordered the dinner Panang chicken entree and paid $10.95 for 1cup of white rice and about 2/3cup of the panang chicken.  Which to me seemed really small. Before I ordered I asked if the dinner comes with an egg or spring roll and was told no. So I ordered 1 portion of the chicken rolls (which weren't good)and got 3 for $4.95. So for 17.95  I got rice, chicken and 3 rolls. The panang  chicken was good but not the very best I've ever had. The best thai food I have ever had was in Orlando and you get 4 rolls, salad and an entre for $14 dollars and the portions are very big. The restaurant itself was clean, the people were nice and the food came out very hot and fast.

Great food, came out quickly, bottled sake was served at the table on ice, and refilled promptly. Service was very accommodating and attentive. Excellent place for a date night, great vegan options, the mango sticky rice dessert was an excellent light finale to the spicy and hearty meal.
Good food
Great food but service could be better. Difficult to place order.
Food is  OK. Nothing special about it.
Friendly staff and great food!
Honestly some of the best Thai food in Tampa. Delicious Curry, great Thai Tea and good service even when relatively busy.

The food was great but our specific waiter wasn't very attentive (I'll concede it was busy). The other waiter we saw literally knew his regular and what they wanted to order without them even saying it....that was impressive, next time we go back we want that guy

I get take out from here at least twice a week.  Great food but extremely small portions.  I have even started getting extra vegetables added to my meal because the portion size is too small.  Adding the extra vegetables makes no difference.  I hate that I'm spending $10-$12 on a meal for something that isn't enough to fill up an adult. I LOVE the food so I would highly suggest going here because it seems the dine in portions are larger.
best thai in downtown

Si-am is a very good Thai restaurant in downtown Tampa. I have never had a negative  experience or a bad meal. Today I the Chicken Cashew Stir Fry, a decent sized serving of chicken, veggies, cashews in a delicious sauce served alongside a half cup or so of fluffy white rice in the shape of a heart. Plate presence is excellent. The meal comes with a spring roll and rice soup. The service is friendly and pretty quick, even during a downtown lunchtime. Only complaints regarded temperature. The soup was slightly less than lukewarm, and the restaurant itself was freezing. I shivered may way through and was happy to get outside to thaw out. Great lunch... but bring a jacket.
Awesome food and great service, one of my favorite places to eat before going to the Straz!
We went twice on our trip to Tampa, so good! Panang curry and drunken noodles are simply outstanding. Clean and quite place. $2 for extra rice. Highly recommend.
The food was great. We celebrated my husband's 50th birthday here & the manager was very helpful & involved. We had a great time.
Went for a friend's birthday. Had a big party and they let us bring entertainment in the form of a murder mystery show.  Great fun.  Good wad great also,  since was impeccable.

Like someone already pointed out, food portion is substantially smaller compared to other Thai restaurants I have been. Pricing is similar or slightly higher then others but proportionally smaller dish is a definite disappointment. Other than this, food taste and look reasonably authentic, service is average and atmosphere is nice. Could someone follow up above issue improves, then might consider returning to this place.
Had shrimp Pad Thai, chicken red curry, and crispy mussel pancakes. All was delicious. Only complaint is the pancakes took longer to come out. Think waiter got distracted.

Friendly staff, well-rounded but not overly complex or extensive menu. Excellent lunch deal includes spring roll and tasty soup. Dishes are flavorful and spiced to order. Everything is delicious, and service is very quick.
Delicious as always
Amazing restaurant with so many antique collection shop!
Good place to celebrate birthday with friends.
One of the best Thai food restaurants in Tampa!
Awesome menu, service and decor.

Since becoming vegan I have become skeptical of Asian restaurants as they all use fish or oyster sauce in everything. And for someone who does not eat meat, and is especially allergic to shellfish, it is always nice to know if there is a dish that I can get. Well what a surprise when the server told me that they had an entire Vegan Menu. What the what? I was so excited I could have peed my pants. And it wasn't just 1 or 2 dishes but an entire side of a menu.
I work nearby so go here often for lunch. The atmosphere and service is great plus the food is fantastic. I've tried all kinds of dishes on the menu and everything has been delicious.
Amazing Thai food, good service. It's always busy at lunch time, but it's worth the wait. If you like spicy food, make sure you try Thai hot++ (plus plus)! 😉🔥
So much yes! Can add the spice yourself so ensure your order is as hot, or mild, as you want. Really fresh ground thai chili peppers!
Food is amazing but little expensive though! Will be back!
I'm not from Tampa but I've been to this restaurant a handful of times when I've been in the area and the food is always good.
One of the best Thai places to go! Highly recommended.
Authentic Thai food at a reasonable price with good service.  A wide variety of dishes for everyone.
Delicious

Excellent service and the food was FANTASTIC.  We had a party of ten walk in and they adapted perfectly to our needs.  The Pad Thai chicken is among my favorites.  A little hotter than average, so be aware.  I love spicy food and the medium was on the heavier side of perfect for me.  On the other hand, my father-in-law got the hot and loved it.  Heat is annoyingly subjective, I suppose.  Anyway, it was a fantastic experience.
Simply the best! Neat and impressive decor (especially the huge dragons). Ask for the Basil fried rice (Medium spicy) to know what perfection tastes like.

Its beautiful and busy place. Great ambience. My favorite here is the pineapple fried rice! However the quantity of each entrée is less compared to other thai places. You might want to order a bit extra. A bit expensive than other thai places in St Petersburg...
Good food and prices

We decided to try a new adventure as far as food goes. This place was next door to the Tampa Theatre where we were going. Despite the extremely slow service by our server, we found the food to be excellent. If ever in the area again, we would definitely return.
I go here a lot for work lunches and everyone is so nice. The food is wonderful!
They have an indoor koi pond which is neat to look at and the food is really good. Read the descriptions though if you don't like seafood because some things contain shrimp that you might not expect.

Very enjoyable.  I got the Tofu and it was really firm and had a great texture.  I tried it with the Amazing Peanut sauce.  Very tasty.  Friend got the Pad Kee Mow and he said it was great.  Most meals come with a soup and spring roll.
Attentive staff, delicious food, it was an amazing experience. Highly recommend if you enjoy spicy food and thai.
One of my favorite Thai places in the Tampa area.  Great lunch spot.

This place is absolutely awesome. Not only is the food amazing, the ownership and staff are amazing as well. I had a long day, stressful day and wanted to find somewhere to relax and unwind with some good food, in a cozy atmosphere. This place made all of that possible. Stephen and his staff went above and beyond to accommodate my party and I. I am extremely satisfied with my visit today. Thank you guys very much! FIVE STARS.
Great food, I order over the phone and carry out to avoid the rush. Highly recommend the Pad Thai and Panang Curry. If you're a fan of spicy, their Thai Hot ++ is wonderful.
This place is just Devine the food is so fresh and delicious the price is amazing. If I could I would give it 5 more stars.
Delicious.  Super crowded for lunch during the week but worth the wait

I had the pineapple fried rice and it was fantastic. Also, went for lunch on a weekday during work and they were fast so no problems getting in and out. This is a perfect place for a quick lunch or a sit down with a client.
The food was ok. But could not really get to the level of some food I ate in Thailand itself.
Wonderful dinner!!! Had the peanut dressing salad and Pad Thai with chicken. Seasoned perfectly!!! Will be back!!
I really like the decor, food was great and prices even better, also customer service and waiters were excellent.
Super friendly service and delicious food! I love Thai food so I am very picky and I was very impressed with this place. Beautiful decor also!

Beautiful place downtown Tampa lots of public parking. We went in for dinner in a weeknight so place was empty. Good quick service and food proportions was right. I’ve had better fried rice before but pad Thai and prig curry was good and spicy!

We decided to try a new adventure as far as food goes. This place was next door to the Tampa Theatre where we were going. Despite the extremely slow service by our server, we found the food to be excellent. If ever in the area again, we would definitely return.
The fish with pepper sauce was wonderful. The satay was dry tough and flavorless

Great food. Nice atmosphere. Tom Ka Soup was good, but wish they had the larger family size option. We'll probably be back. However, I forget most of the details a few days later, no not that memorable.
Genuinely good food.
Great duck dishes and great ambiance
Nice, cool atmosphere. Good prices. Good food.
Good food, service and reasonable prices!

This review is long overdue, as I've been going to lunch at Si-am for years, almost every week.  The food is great, the staff is very nice, and they're usually pretty quick during lunch.  My favorites are the chicken massaman curry, chicken fried rice, steamed dumplings, and crab rangoon.
Great selection and prices. Heat of dishes can bre adjusted. Even nice desserts!
The food is incredible and very authentic! I love the vibe of the restaurant and the staff is very pleasant!

Our son got us a gift certificate for this restaurant and we found out it's the best Thai food we have had. Very nice atmosphere and Steve the owner was a very nice guy. He recommended new dishes we have never had. The food is to die for. Will be taking our kids when they come to visit

I've never had anything short of a lovely experience coming here! Every dish I've tried has exceeded expectations, and I'm still eagerly working through the menu. Stephen is easily among the most attentive and inviting business owners I've met—it’s always great getting to chat with him. If you like Thai cuisine, or just excellent food in general, Si-am is at the top of my list in Tampa for a perfectly enjoyable meal.

We love going to see the owner Steve! His food is amazing yet his service is over the top excellent! It is the perfect place to go before going to the Historic Tampa Theater. On our last visit, he sat down with us to tell us about the history of Tampa. That purple drink is his creation of Butterfly Tea which is AMAZING!

The BEST Thai restaurant in Tampa, Florida. The food is DELICIOUS and the staff are so nice and welcoming! Food ordered for pick-up is plenty and tastes just as good as dining in! Their chicken panang dish is out of this world. By far my favorite place!!!
Delicious food and very reasonable prices. Within walking distance of the Straz Center (7 min walk)
Excellent food, service, and atmosphere.  Highly recommend it!!

One of the best Thai restaraunts around & so close to the Straz. Worked out perfect to eat 1st before the show. We saw Hamilton. Reasonable pricing. Very clean & wait staff was excellent. We will be back
Very good food and great service! Would recommend to anyone!

Yes Yes and Yes! This is a Great Family owned Business. They pay great attention to every detail. They will be moving at the end of their lease, I hope they move to Dade City,  I'll eat there a few times a month or more!
Took my two oldest daughters. We loved it. The Amazing dish. That is the name, was as it names says. AMAZING.. Look forward to returning.
The food was awesome!!!

My wife and I have been to Si-am Thai several times in the past few months. The food is excellent as is the atmosphere. We have never had trouble getting a table. It is in Downtown Tampa right next to the Tampa Theatre. I highly recommend stopping here for some great Thai food.
I have had delicious food every single time I've eaten there!
Good Thai food
Food was wonderful. Service was great. Serving sizes for lunch were perfect.
Good food, nice atmosphere!
one of the best and cheap Thai food I ever had
Great thai food! Busy at lunch time but worth the small wait.
The best in town! I love this place. Excellent food and awesome staff!
Service was great. Friendly servers and food was outstanding. Spent a great family get together there.
The Thai food here is exceptional.

We eat here usually once a week or so and the food is always good. I didn't think I liked Thai food until my co-workers convinced me to eat here. I usually get the pepper steak or the garlic pepper stir fry with no spice. Both have a really nice flavor. I also really like their chicken fried rice. Their entrees come with a chicken and rice soup and a mini spring roll. I've also ordered the crab Rangoon and hate when I have to share it! If you're going at lunch, get there early, because they tend to get very busy around noon. The servers are nice and do a good job.
Best Thai hands down!
So delicious, great service, very nice staff
Amazing food and amazing service. Definitely one of those places I’ll never forget.
Customer service and food was sooo good!!
Food was delicious and the staff and managers were wonderful.  Price's are competitive and the lunch comes with soup and a small,  but delicious,  spring roll.

Friendly staff, tasty Thai food. Pretty good menu though I wish I could have gotten papaya salad. One thing - the seat backs in the booths are quite loose. My friend moves as he talks and suddenly we found ourselves bouncing around because a man in the booth behind us was upset with the slight movement and decided to push back repeatedly/dramatically. Had he acted like an adult it probably would have been a non-issue.
Very good Thai food in downtown Tampa.  This place gets very crowded at lunch time. The portions are large and always tasty.
Best downtown
Ate here for lunch on a business trip to downtown Tampa.  Possibly the best shrimp fried rice I've had.  Very good food, and quick service.  Place was packed out by noon.  Get there early.
The food was delicious I will definitely be going again

Amazing food. Cool atmosphere with very vibrid and interactive art work. Has a cool style and is very nice to look at. The food is very good as well. Fast and efficient service. Cool waiters as well. i definitely recommend this restaurant if you’re in the area

As a frequent traveler to Thailand, married to a Thai woman with life long Thai friendships I can truly say the food was exceptional, service prompt and polite and décor enchanting. Sizzling duck was superb.
Thai fried rice and panang curry were very good
Food was delicious.   Has the crab fried rice and while you couldn't really see the crab as it was shredded and mixed into the rice,  you could definitely taste it.
The service was very slow, food was average, and the cost was a bit high.
Great food and service.
Great food excellent service always consistent

The flavors of the two dishes I ordered were on point!  I've gone to a few Thai restaurants in this area and normally one of the two dishes I order is ok, or both are really bad.  This place is legit!
Beautiful space. Amazing green curry. Lots of fresh veggies. Great customer service.
Delicious food and pretty atmosphere.  It is conveniently located near Tampa Theater.
Excellent food and service. Good atmosphere.
Super friendly staff. The server was very attentive.  My Panang curry was great. It’s located right in the center of everything. I’ll definitely go back.
Disappointed in the place. The reviews are overrated. Ordered the crab fried rice and pad Thai, both was a disappointment.
Very friendly staff, great food and value. Red pork on anything is a good start. Worth the trip!
Friendly staff, great food. Go for the lunch special with soup and a spring roll.
Best Duck that I have ever ate. The owners are both very talented chefs. The husband was very friendly and I got to have a nice conversation with him
Great Thai food. Quick and friendly service staff.

Great Thai spot tucked away next to the Tampa theatre. Inside is really nice, great decor. They had a lot to offer on the menu. I ordered the crispy duck. For you all that love heat, they have different levels of heat, all the way to Thai hot. I'm not big on heat so I got mine mild. The duck came out sizzling and the armoa was heavenly. It tasted just as good. Will definitely be back!
Great thai food and wonderful atmosphere and staff. The owner is always on site and such a nice guy. A downtown favorite and must go to restaurant! I strongly recommend!
This is my go to place for Pad Thai and Pineapple fried rice.  Would recommend to anybody just be cautious when ordering "Thai-Hot" anything.
Amazing decor, friendly staff and delicious food
Love this place. Have gone to eat dinner here many times. Staff is always friendly and food is delicious.
Delicious food. Excellent service. 10/10
Delicious, good service, nice vibe.
Good spicey food comfortable atmosphere
Food was really good. It would have been nice if I didn't have to fight with the mosquitoes eating my food.
The pepper steak needs to have some steak in it very little and what was in the pepper steak was not chewable
Great thai restaurant downtown.
Food oustanding. Authentic and Fresh. Great date night. They make you feel special.

I eat here at least once a week for lunch, and have done so for several years.  You know it must be good if the monks are eating here.  Great food, excellent service!  If I was to say anything critical, it would be that their prices have gone up recently, but it seems like everyone downtown is raising prices for their lunch menus.  That and the spicing isn't consistent.  One day "medium" will be "meh" and the next time it will be hot.  That being said, they do a great job and the food is always excellent.  I highly recommend!
Tried this place next to the Tampa Theater....it was better than expected.
I love this place! I have been here at least 20 times, I always get the pad thai. This photo is the pad thai vegetable hot. I will definetly be back.
Good Thai food
Their sampler is really tasty!!
Excellent Food and Service
Excellent
Best Thai in the downtown area! Great lunch deals too

Really good food! I love curries and they had very flavorful Masaman! I ordered Thai Hot as I love spicy, but it really wasn't even hot. That would be my only "complaint" which is really not a huge deal.
(Translated by Google) I love youuuu !!!!!  (Original) I love youuuu!!!!!
The place is clean and nice. The food is not bad, but too sweet for Thai people.
Not the best Thai food in Tampa, but good. This is setup as a more formal dining experience than other alternatives. Good prices. The service was quite slow after being seated. Very nice staff.
Been here many times. Food is always good. Service is always professional. But my favorite part is the atmosphere; the decor is very tasteful. Will continue to visit this cool restaurant.
Excellent, fresh food. Great price. Friendly staff.
Wish I knew of this place sooner!  Quality food and service.
Longggg wait time, small portion, staff too busy to care.  NOT going back.
Awesome Thai-Food! Go for the basil rolls and curry
Fried Rice was under-cooked. Paid extra for shrimp in the rice, but there was only 2 in the entire bowl. Portions are not worth what you pay for. I would not recommend this place.
Top notch good and service

I definitely agree the food was great but customer service is not. They do not have a host at the front door to greet you it also seems a bit unorganized because of it. If you order to go make sure you walk to the back where they are processing payments or else you’ll be there forever!!
The tom kha gai is heavenly!

During my long stay on downtown, I visited this place almost everyday. Staff is very friendly and service is quick. Prices are affordable.  The best dishes is drunken noodles. I like, their starters and deserts as well. I recommend this to all.
Jus got take out but the food was excellent and the service was even better. In a timely fashion
GREAT food GREAT service NICE people!
Very long waiting line. I stayed here and waited for almost 40 mins for a garlic and black pepper beef. Only two waiters and I suppose there is only one chef. Very uncomfortable experience.

I am on my lunch break, I ordered 2 soups, and only got 1, and when I tried to ask for my soup, the Asian woman yelled what!! She was very rude , as i am speaking, my partner has finished his soup, and i still haven't gotten mine. We had my one year old son, and he was never  given a high chair. I have been here before,  and I'm very disappointed of this experience. They just brought the check,  and it had two soups, and the man asked if I wanted the soup taken out. Um, of course!
It was good.
Delicious spring roll and drunken noodles, friendly staff, good beers and very reasonably priced. Nice presentation and relaxing atmosphere but I imagine lunch is probably their busy time.

I can say, I have had alot of thai in my day. Ordered the seafood pad thai. It just really wasn't that good. No flavor. The sea food in the dish was tiny and not local. Just not anything special I would say. Though the restaurant was very pretty for a nice sit down meal. Everyone else on here says they are amazing. Maybe I just got a dinged meal. Anyplace that can't put a little pride into their sea food however isn't saying much. For what we paid for the meal, $20 per plate, should get you real sea food. That is all.
Good food, very good prices

We just arrived in Tampa and had a hankering for Thai cuisine. Si-am was close to our hotel so we decide to check it out. They have a great assortment of beers (Singha, Kirin, and some specialty local brew). I had the red that was very tasty. We started with fried calamari, and spring rolls (both veggie and chicken). These were all basic. The calamari was underwhelming - only the rings and battered in a way that made them look like onion rings. My favorite calamari are the little squid like calamari and there were none to be found sadly. I ordered the Massaman Curry and the Drunken Noodles. They gave us an option of heat; light, medium, hot and Thai hot. We picked light noodles and medium Curry. The Curry definitely had a kick that I appreciated but I don't think I'd want to experience Thai hot hah I might not make it through. I tried the Thai Iced Tea that was incredibly tasty but it generally always is (I'm a huge fan). The server was very attentive and while he took the time to split our bills without asking he did jumble up some items on wrong checks so we venmo-ed each other which was odd.  Overall, if you want solid Thai cuisine, I recommend Si-am.

Food is awesome. Great variety of food dishes in the menu. We enjoyed Fresh basil rolls, steamed dumpling, satay chicken, mixed sea food soup, fried rice with curries, Pad Thai Noodle and ice creams. It's always a great dining experience each time we visit this restaurant. Great atmosphere and friendly service.
Local. Good ppl with good food.

Delicious food, quick service, very friendly staff. I loved the pad se ew, and appreciated the option to choose my spice level. I also got the sticky rice with mango for dessert, which was heavenly. We were one of maybe four tables and service was incredibly slow, especially for a restaurant in the middle of downtown at lunch time. My lunch companion quite literally had to ask for her food to be brought out (some 20 minutes after my food had been delivered) when it became clear that they'd forgotten about her meal.  Her fried rice was room temperature and had solidified into a mass. Clearly it had been prepared for some time but was not brought to our table. I had flavorful but lukewarm soup and we shared a tasty small plate of fried tofu. The small portion of rice soup and mini-spring roll that comes with lunch are a nice touch, though the roasted garlic used in the soup was very, very strong. We also enjoyed the Thai tea. Had the food been served timely and hot, I'd be giving a much different review.
